as a division of a specific set of SC's to be taken?<BR>&gt;</P>
<P>The game has a negotiation phase which is broken down into two areas; 
the=20
assembly room where all players ( including AI ) start, and the meeting 
rooms=20
where players go off to negotiate in private. Up to six players can be 
in a=20
meeting room at one time. Within the meeting room human players can 
construct=20
offers for other human players and also AI players. At the same time 
players=20
will receive offers from other human players and AI players. These 
offers can=20
include allying ( or not ), attacking, moves, convoys, DMZs, bounces, 
and=20
hearsay. You and the other players, both human and AI, are free to 
except or=20
decline these offers. But in no way are you or the AI players bound to 
their=20
acceptance. The AI prioritizes its goals and compares that with offers 
made to=20
control its movement. The best AI ( we will have three ) will plan and 
look more=20
turns out.</P>
